r more problematized perspectives on the issue of sexual harassment. This book opens for new understandings of sexual harassment by bringing researchers, writers, and policymakers in the Nordic region into dialogue in an ambitious volume. It asks what role juridical frameworks can and should play in prevention and raises questions about how the image of Nordic states - as gender equal, colour blind and with strong welfare - affects the work against sexual harassment in the region. Re-imagining definitions of justice, violence, exploitation and work, this book offers knowledge of immediate importance for everyone working to prevent sexual harassment, through research, policy making, or in everyday practice.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sexual Abuse & Harassment.2bisacsh1 aAli, Sumaya Jirde, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAliki, Silas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAnanda Lodahl, Mads, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAntonsdóttir, Hildur Fjóla, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBjarnegård, Elin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCalvo, Dolores, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEldén, Åsa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGarrett, Paul Russell, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHambro, Cathinka Dahl, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHearn, Jeff, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ct